"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":-0.73,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"weak","read":"Only -0.73\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory).","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.61,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"ok","read":"Moderate leverage (D/E 0.61\u00d7, interest cover 3.8\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":22.95,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 23% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":25.9,"pe_percentile":74.0,"median_pe":17.8,"earnings_yield_pct":3.86,"pb":3.19,"ev_ebitda":25.42,"quality_score":36.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":10.5,"peg":2.48,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 74-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 25.9\u00d7 earnings for ~10% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22482.48\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[71.72,71.72,71.72,72.16,72.29,72.29,72.29,72.43,70.84,68.19,68.27,62.51],"latest_pct":62.51,"chg_1y_pp":-9.92},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[0.0,0.0,0.08,0.26,0.67,0.23,0.17,0.72,1.89,3.36,4.92,9.5],"latest_pct":9.5,"chg_1y_pp":8.78},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[0.0,0.02,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.25,0.25,0.25,0.49,1.82,1.63,2.91],"latest_pct":2.91,"chg_1y_pp":2.66},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 202